title.rendered: UAE vs Canada, World Cup Qualifier Play-Off 2023: Fantasy Team, Probable Playing XIs, Pitch Report & Fantasy Tips

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team on basis of probable XIs, recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable XIs

UAE: Muhammad Waseem (c), Aryan Lakra, Vriitya Aravind (wk), Rameez Shahzad, Rohan Mustafa, Asif Khan, Aayan Afzal Khan, Karthik Meiyappan, Junaid Siddique, Zahoor Khan, Matiullah Khan

Canada: Aaron Johnson, Pargat Singh, Matthew Spoors, Srimantha Wijeratne (wk), Nicholas Kirton, Harsh Thaker, Nikhil Dutta, Saad Bin Zafar (c), Ravinderpal Singh, Kaleem Sana, Jeremy Gordon

Pitch Report

Venue: Wanderers Cricket Ground, Windhoek

(Based on last three games)

1st innings average score: 224

2nd innings average score: 249

Wickets per innings: 8

Type: Slow wicket

Wins

Batting 1st: 67%

Batting 2nd: 33%

Also Read:

Gujarat vs Chennai, Indian T20 League 2023 Fantasy Tips

Hyderabad vs Rajasthan, Indian T20 League 2023 Fantasy Tips

Bangalore vs Mumbai, Indian T20 League 2023 Fantasy Tips

Fantasy Tips of The Day

The following data is based on both ODIs and List A.

Nikhil Dutta has been contributing points with both bat and ball. In addition to scalping 16 wickets in the last nine matches, he scored two half-centuries in the last four innings.

Kaleem Sana is in red-hot form: two five-fors and a four-for in the last six matches, collecting a total of 20 wickets at a stunning strike rate of 13.5.

Saad Bin Zafar picked 19 wickets in the last nine matches, also generating points for 120 runs during this period.

Srimantha Wijeratne has been a fantasy delight of late. Not only did he slam four fifties in his last seven outings but also inflicted 15 dismissals.

Muhammad Waseem’s performances in the last 10 outings are a mixed bag. While he smashed a century and two half-centuries, he also had scores of 0, 0, 1, and 2.

Vriitya Aravind featured in the Best11 in three of the last four games, scoring 184 runs.

Asif Khan scored two centuries in the last three matches, which helped him collect 423 runs at 53 in the last 10 matches.

Junaid Siddique was UAE’s highest wicket-taker (43) in the League 2 of the WC qualifiers. Moreover, he has been effective with the ball lately, grabbing 17 wickets in the last 11 games.

Seven half-centuries and one century were scored in the last three matches at the venue. Meanwhile, pacers scalped 60% of the wickets.
